      • User

        public User(java.lang.String username,
            java.lang.String firstName,
            java.lang.String lastName,

            BatchType batchType,
            java.util.List<AssociateAttendance> attendance,
            java.util.List<AssociateTask> tasks,
            UserRole userRole)
        Constructor for User object. This constructor is specifically designed to be used for creating a User who is an associate. Initializes all instance variables except for ID, as that is automatically generated on creation.
        Parameters:
        username - String that represents the username of the User object.
        firstName - String that represents the first name of the User object.
        lastName - String that represents the last name of the User object.
        hashedPassword - String that represents the hashedPassword of the User object.
        batchType - BatchType object that represents the specific BatchType that the User belongs to.
        attendance - List containing AssociateAttendence objects that keeps track of the user's attendance.
        tasks - List containing AssociateTask objects that keeps track of the user's tasks.
        userRole - UserRole object that keeps track of the user's specific role.

      • User

        public User(java.lang.String username,
            java.lang.String firstName,
            java.lang.String lastName,
            java.lang.String hashedPassword,
            UserRole userRole)
        Constructor for User object. This constructor is meant to be used to create users who aren't associates. Initializes the username, firsName, lastName, hashedPassword, and userRole variables of the user object based on the supplied values.
        Parameters:
        username - String that represents the username of the User object.
        firstName - String that represents the first name of the User object.
        lastName - String that represents the last name of the User object.
        hashedPassword - String that represents the hashedPassword of the User object.
        userRole - UserRole object that keeps track of the user's specific role.
